HEADWORD: Acotyledon
<hw>A*cot`y*le"don</hw> <pr>(#; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'a</grk> priv. + <?/ anything cup-shaped. See
<er>Cotyledon</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant which has no
cotyledons, as the dodder and all flowerless plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acotyledonous</ent>⟦br⟧
